title: Tree
---
<<once>>
*Vera places her hand against the tree
A voice in Vera's Mind: So it is true.
A voice in Vera's Mind: The presence I have felt has been you.

-> Hello?
 {A voice: Welcome Vera.
  A voice: I have been expecting you.}
-> Who said that?
 {A voice: Who is less important when understanding the galaxy as I do.
  // Clear variable names are also essential
  <<set $tree_galaxy_mentioned to true>>}
-> Show yourself!
 {A voice: Look around you, young one.
  A voice: I do not require to show myself as you've seen me already.}
<<endonce>>

<<if $tree_galaxy_mentioned>>
-> The galaxy? What do you mean?
 {Tree: My presence has existed for eons.
  Tree: I know who and what you are, Vera.}
<<endif>>

<<once>>
-> How do you know my name? Who are you?
 {Tree: I am known by many names. All of which have now been lost to time.
  Tree: My understanding of the galaxy far exceeds the very age of this planet we inhabit.
  Tree: I know by your soul who you are, Vera.
  <<set $tree_galaxy_mentioned to true>>}
-> I don't understand. What do you mean?
 {Tree: The very Forest around you.
  Tree: I exist within every tree, every leaf, and every branch.
  Tree: I have lived for eons, reaching my roots into the very core of this planet.
  Tree: My existence is tied to this planet and so I know of every creature that walks its surface.
  Tree: Even you, Vera.}
<<endonce>>

<<once>>
-> You know nothing of my past.
 {Tree: I know everything.
  Tree: Your desire yo please your father but always falling short.
  Tree: Your broken heart from the fracturing of your family.
  Tree: The pain you carry for being born as someone who you are not.
  Tree: You radiate your strife like warmth from the sun.}
-> How could you possibly know who I am?
 {Tree: Your very soul resonates here, my girl.
  Tree: No matter how one was born, it is their soul that holds their identity.
  Tree: You're destined for something grander, but you waste your time seeking the dead.}
-> I am not some book you can read. What makes you think I would listen to you?
 {Tree: You will listen.
  Tree: Not with your ears, but your soul.
  Tree: It knows the truth, like it always has.
  Tree: Your birth didn't define who you are, and so your soul will lead you to the truth.}
<<endonce>>

Then what must I do?

Tree: Find the fire in your heart.
Tree: Seek out the heat and burn away the pain.
Tree: Your grief is the only thing holding you hostage now.
-> I've already burned away my grief! Your words are empty.
 {Tree: Then you are truly lost.
  Tree: I can't allow you to leave this place.
  Tree: Be at peace as you fade into oblivion.
  *Vera dies as the tree consumes her
  <<set $ending_vera_dies to true>>
  <<set $ending_screen_color to "red">>}
-> I cannot. I don't know who I will become if I do.
  {*The tree goes dim leaving Vera alone in the jungle.}
-> You're right. I must let go.
  {Tree: As all things die, all things live.
  *A bright light consumes Vera.
  <<set $ending_vera_enlightened to true>>
  <<set $ending_screen_color to "white">>}
===

